==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peltier effect
<hw>Pel`tier" ef*fect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After <person>Jean C. A.
<etsep>Peltier</etsep></person>, French physicist, the
discoverer.]</ety> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The production or absorption
of heat at the junction of two metals on the passage of a current. Heat
generated by the passage of the current in one direction will be
absorbed if the current is reversed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peltier's cross</ent>⟦br⟧
